# crates/ctx-cage/src/proxy.rs

Host-side API proxy: the only egress path for the offline cage. Listens
on a UNIX socket bind-mounted into the cage at `/run/ctx/api.sock`; the
in-cage relay forwards `127.0.0.1:8080` to it. Per connection: reads the
HTTP/1.1 request head, rewrites it, dials upstream over TLS, and pumps
bytes both ways.

Two auth postures via `ProxyConfig.api_key`: `Some(key)` strips any
client credential and injects the real `x-api-key` host-side (cage only
sees a placeholder); `None` passes the client's own `Authorization`
through unmodified (subscription-OAuth posture — the bound credential
authenticates, proxy is just the controlled egress).

Header rewriting (`rewrite_head`, in `head.rs`) is a pure function over
text; TLS/sockets are isolated behind the `Upstream` trait seam. Default
impl `SocatUpstream` shells out to `socat - OPENSSL:<host>:443,verify=1,...`
with a 24h (`-t 86400`) timeout — this long half-close timeout is
deliberate (referenced as "the ADR-028 lesson"); no TLS stack lives in
this crate.

Diagnostics go to `cfg.log_path` via `log_line`/`log_stdio`, never to
inherited stdio — during interactive runs stdio is the host terminal in
raw mode owned by `pty.rs`'s PTY relay thread, and writing there directly
would race/corrupt the display. Logging failures are swallowed, never
propagated or panicking.

Key functions: `serve_conn<U: Upstream>(client, cfg, upstream) ->
Result<(), CageError>` handles one connection (head read, rewrite, dial,
bidirectional pump via a spawned thread for the client→upstream
direction). `serve<U>(listener, cfg, upstream, stop: &AtomicBool)` is the
accept loop — nonblocking, one thread per connection, polls `stop` every
`ACCEPT_IDLE` (20ms) to allow clean shutdown.

`pub(crate) fn pump` is reused by the interactive PTY relay in
`lifecycle::run::pty` — best-effort byte copy, silently stops on any
read/write error, always flushes on exit.

Coupling: `ProxyConfig` and the placeholder-credential convention must
stay consistent with whatever code constructs the in-cage relay pointing
at `/run/ctx/api.sock`.